title: Tennant interviewing Sheen
body:
You want to listen to David Tennant interviewing Michael Sheen, don’t you? Of COURSE you do. It’s completely delightful.

Things I love about it:

1) Their anecdote about the tediousness of the photo shoot they did together, in which Sheen is more the demon (“I wanted to kill everybody in the room, including myself”) and Tennant more the angel (Sheen says Tennant, being a “lovely person,” talked nicely to the journalists when Sheen was being grumpily silent).

2) Sheen’s dad worked for a while as a professional Jack Nicholson look-alike. We could not make up this kind of thing.

3) Even these two have had moments–many moments–of thinking they were terrible at what they did and/or just couldn’t do it anymore, have forgotten lines on stage, wanted to quit and walk away. When the rest of us feel that way about our jobs, we should remember we are in excellent and talented company.

4) Direct quote, when they get around to discussing Good Omens:
Sheen: So this was what brought us together, into the, uh–into the new love story for the twenty-first century!
Tennant: Exactly!
🖤
